# IMAP (RFC 3501, tcp:143) control-channel command. Client sends `a001 LOGIN alice secret\r\n` to the
# server. The whole message is kept verbatim (byte-perfect); the first line is parsed for display
# (kind/tag/command/status/text). IMAP lines are TAG-prefixed: a tagged command/response `<tag> ...`, an
# untagged `* ...`, or a continuation `+ ...` — see the crafted response tests in IMAP.spec.ts.
# source: real capture — python:3.12-slim container, a python socket listening on 127.0.0.1:143 and a
# second python socket connecting and sending `a001 LOGIN alice secret\r\n`, over the ethernet lo
# interface, captured with tcpdump (all-zero loopback MACs, ethertype 0800, IPv4/TCP dst port 143 with
# timestamp options). This frame is the client's tagged LOGIN command.
